		<content translate="true">How the Brain Makes Meaning</content>
	</text>
	<text id="nav_text" x="207" y="425" width="564" height="" autosize="H" style="PROMPT" visible="false" fx="PROMPT_SHOW" hidefx="PROMPT_HIDE">
		<content translate="true">Click a &lt;B&gt;Lesson&lt;/B&gt; or &lt;B&gt;Activity&lt;/B&gt; to learn more.</content>
	</text>
	<section id="presentation_text" align="LEFT" spacing="0x10" autospace="true" columns="0" exclusive="false" expanded="true">
		<text id="text01" x="350" y="60" width="380" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="true" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">As children experience new situations, their brains strive to make sense of their experience by creating meaning.</content>
		</text>
		<text id="text02" x="350" y="85.2" width="380" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">1960 "Visual Cliff" study:</content>
		</text>
		<text id="text03" x="350" y="114.8" width="404" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">&lt;LI&gt;6-month-old babies stop at the edge of the cliff and reach across in an attempt to make sense of the situation. &lt;/LI&gt;</content>
		</text>
		<text id="text04" x="350" y="160" width="403" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">&lt;LI&gt;Babies learned to crawl across the glass. &lt;/LI&gt;</content>
		</text>
		<text id="text05" x="350" y="160" width="395" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">&lt;LI&gt;Babies had to re-learn to cross the glass when they began walking.&lt;/LI&gt;</content>
		</text>
		<text id="text06" x="350" y="205.2" width="382" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">&lt;LI&gt;4-day-old goats would never cross the visual cliff, even when coaxed by people or enticed with food. &lt;/LI&gt;</content>
		</text>
		<text id="text07" x="350" y="250.4" width="382" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">Brains work to make meaning and learn from experience.</content>
		</text>
	</section>
